---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';

// SEO-optimized description
const metaDescription = "Learn microservices architecture and AI agent integration through a real-world Personal Finance Management System. Practical guides on Domain-Driven Design, event-driven architecture, service mesh, and AI-ready microservices for FinTech and SaaS applications.";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={metaDescription} />
		
		<!-- Additional SEO -->
		<meta name="keywords" content="microservices architecture, AI agents, domain-driven design, event-driven architecture, FinTech microservices, Spring Boot, NestJS, service mesh, kafka, rabbitmq, personal finance system" />
		<link rel="canonical" href="https://yourdomain.com/" />
		
		<!-- Structured Data -->
		<script type="application/ld+json">
		{
			"@context": "https://schema.org",
			"@type": "TechArticle",
			"headline": "Learn Microservices Architecture with Real-World FinTech Examples",
			"description": "{metaDescription}",
			"author": {
				"@type": "Person",
				"name": "Your Name",
				"url": "https://linkedin.com/in/delose/"
			}
		}
		</script>
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<!-- Hero Section -->
			<section class="hero">
				<h1>Build Production-Ready Microservices & AI-Powered Systems</h1>
				<p class="subtitle">
					Learn through a real-world <strong>Personal Finance Management System</strong> built with 10+ microservices, event-driven architecture, and AI-ready design patterns.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- Value Proposition -->
			<section class="value-prop">
				<h2>From FinTech Engineer to Your Learning Companion</h2>
				<p>
					I've recently joined the FinTech industry and I'm sharing everything I've learned about building scalable, resilient microservices. This isn't theory‚Äîit's battle-tested architecture patterns from a production-grade personal finance system.
				</p>
			</section>

			<!-- The Project -->
			<section class="project-overview">
				<h2>The PFMS Project: Your Microservices Playground üõ∞Ô∏è</h2>
				<p>
					The <strong>Personal Finance Management System (PFMS)</strong> is a comprehensive, polyglot microservices application that demonstrates enterprise-grade patterns:
				</p>
				
				<div class="architecture-grid">
					<div class="arch-card">
						<h3>üèóÔ∏è Multi-Language Ecosystem</h3>
						<p><strong>Spring Boot</strong> (API Gateway, Budget, Notification), <strong>NestJS</strong> (Account, Transaction), <strong>Go</strong> (User Service), <strong>Python</strong> (Reporting), <strong>React</strong> (UI)</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="arch-card">
						<h3>üì° Event-Driven Architecture</h3>
						<p><strong>Kafka</strong> for async communication, <strong>RabbitMQ</strong> for message brokering, event sourcing patterns for financial transactions</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="arch-card">
						<h3>üîç Service Discovery & Config</h3>
						<p><strong>Eureka</strong> and <strong>Consul</strong> for service registry, centralized <strong>Config Server</strong> with Git-backed configurations</p>
					</div>
					
					<div class="arch-card">
						<h3>üõ°Ô∏è Security & Observability</h3>
						<p><strong>JWT authentication</strong>, custom actuators, caching strategies, Docker-ready deployments with health monitoring</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- What You'll Learn -->
			<section class="learning-outcomes">
				<h2>What You'll Master Here</h2>
				
				<div class="two-column">
					<div class="learn-column">
						<h3>For Developers Leveling Up</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>Domain-Driven Design (DDD)</strong> in practice‚Äîsee how bounded contexts map to microservices in a financial domain</li>
							<li><strong>Event-driven patterns</strong> with Kafka producers/consumers and async processing after DB commits</li>
							<li><strong>Polyglot persistence</strong>‚ÄîPostgreSQL, MySQL, and strategic database-per-service design</li>
							<li><strong>API Gateway patterns</strong> with routing, load balancing, and JWT security</li>
							<li><strong>Service mesh fundamentals</strong> using Eureka and Consul for real-world service discovery</li>
							<li><strong>Resilience patterns</strong>‚Äîcircuit breakers, retries, and graceful degradation</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
					
					<div class="learn-column">
						<h3>AI-Ready Architecture (Coming Soon)</h3>
						<ul>
							<li><strong>AI agent integration patterns</strong> for financial workflows (budget recommendations, expense categorization)</li>
							<li><strong>Microservices as AI interfaces</strong>‚Äîhow to expose your services for LLM consumption</li>
							<li><strong>Event-driven AI</strong>‚Äîtriggering AI workflows from domain events</li>
							<li><strong>Building AI-powered SaaS</strong> features on top of microservices foundations</li>
							<li><strong>RAG systems for financial data</strong>‚Äîvector stores, embeddings, and context-aware AI</li>
						</ul>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Microservices 101 -->
			<section class="microservices-101">
				<h2>Microservices Architecture: The Foundation</h2>
				<p>
					Instead of building one large "monolith" where everything is tightly coupled, microservices architecture breaks your application into independent, self-contained services that communicate through APIs and events.
				</p>
				
				<div class="benefits-list">
					<div class="benefit">
						<h4>üéØ Independent Deployment</h4>
						<p>Update the Budget Service without touching Transaction Service. Deploy on your own schedule, reduce deployment risk.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="benefit">
						<h4>üìà Selective Scaling</h4>
						<p>Scale only what needs scaling. If transaction processing gets heavy, scale just that service, not the entire app.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="benefit">
						<h4>üîß Technology Flexibility</h4>
						<p>Use Spring Boot for enterprise features, NestJS for real-time processing, Go for high-performance user management‚Äîbest tool for each job.</p>
					</div>
					<div class="benefit">
						<h4>ü§ñ AI Integration Ready</h4>
						<p>Each service can be enhanced with AI capabilities independently. Add LLM-powered budgeting without refactoring your entire codebase.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- CTA Section -->
			<section class="cta">
				<h2>Start Learning from Real Code</h2>
				<p>
					Explore the blog for deep-dives into specific patterns, or dive straight into the <a href="https://github.com/yourusername/personal-finance-management-system" target="_blank" rel="noopener">PFMS GitHub repository</a> to see production-quality microservices code.
				</p>
				<div class="cta-buttons">
					<a href="/blog" class="btn-primary">Read the Blog</a>
					<a href="https://github.com/yourusername/personal-finance-management-system" class="btn-secondary" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Explore the Code</a>
				</div>
			</section>

			<!-- Expertise Signal -->
			<section class="about">
				<p class="expertise-note">
					<em>Written by a FinTech engineer who nuked all graveyard projects to focus on what matters: microservices that scale and AI agents that deliver value. Connect with me on <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/delose/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">LinkedIn</a>.</em>
				</p>
			</section>
		</main>
		<Footer />

		<style>
			main {
				max-width: 1200px;
				margin: 0 auto;
				padding: 2rem 1rem;
				line-height: 1.7;
			}

			.hero {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
				text-align: center;
			}

			.hero h1 {
				font-size: 2.5rem;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				color: #1a202c;
			}

			.subtitle {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
				color: #4a5568;
				max-width: 800px;
				margin: 0 auto;
			}

			.value-prop {
				background: #f7fafc;
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.value-prop h2 {
				color: #2d3748;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.project-overview {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.architecture-grid {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
				gap: 1.5rem;
				margin-top: 1.5rem;
			}

			.arch-card {
				background: white;
				border: 2px solid #e2e8f0;
				border-radius: 8px;
				padding: 1.5rem;
			}

			.arch-card h3 {
				color: #2b6cb0;
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
				font-size: 1.1rem;
			}

			.learning-outcomes {
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.two-column {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
				gap: 2rem;
				margin-top: 1.5rem;
			}

			.learn-column h3 {
				color: #2d3748;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.learn-column ul {
				list-style: none;
				padding: 0;
			}

			.learn-column li {
				margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
				padding-left: 1.5rem;
				position: relative;
			}

			.learn-column li:before {
				content: "‚Üí";
				position: absolute;
				left: 0;
				color: #3182ce;
				font-weight: bold;
			}

			.microservices-101 {
				background: #edf2f7;
				padding: 2rem;
				border-radius: 8px;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.benefits-list {
				display: grid;
				grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(250px, 1fr));
				gap: 1.5rem;
				margin-top: 1.5rem;
			}

			.benefit h4 {
				color: #2c5282;
				margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
			}

			.cta {
				text-align: center;
				padding: 3rem 1rem;
				background: linear-gradient(135deg, #667eea 0%, #764ba2 100%);
				color: white;
				border-radius: 12px;
				margin-bottom: 3rem;
			}

			.cta h2 {
				color: white;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
			}

			.cta-buttons {
				display: flex;
				gap: 1rem;
				justify-content: center;
				margin-top: 2rem;
				flex-wrap: wrap;
			}

			.btn-primary, .btn-secondary {
				padding: 0.75rem 2rem;
				border-radius: 6px;
				text-decoration: none;
				font-weight: 600;
				transition: transform 0.2s;
			}

			.btn-primary {
				background: white;
				color: #5a67d8;
			}

			.btn-secondary {
				background: transparent;
				color: white;
				border: 2px solid white;
			}

			.btn-primary:hover, .btn-secondary:hover {
				transform: translateY(-2px);
			}

			.about {
				text-align: center;
				color: #718096;
				font-size: 0.95rem;
			}

			.expertise-note a {
				color: #3182ce;
				text-decoration: none;
			}

			.expertise-note a:hover {
				text-decoration: underline;
			}

			h2 {
				color: #2d3748;
				margin-bottom: 1rem;
				font-size: 1.875rem;
			}

			@media (max-width: 768px) {
				.hero h1 {
					font-size: 1.875rem;
				}

				.subtitle {
					font-size: 1.1rem;
				}

				.cta-buttons {
					flex-direction: column;
					align-items: center;
				}

				.btn-primary, .btn-secondary {
					width: 100%;
					max-width: 300px;
				}
			}
		</style>
	</body>
</html>